Where do all the clusters map in Cluster 2?

Load libraries.

library(Seurat)
library(tidyverse)
library(RColorBrewer)

Load umap of cluster.

load("/Volumes/all_ssd/20220414-seurat/flox-integr-res-0.0120/flox-2-res-0.056/umap-by-cluster-flox-2-res-0.056.Robj")
umap.2 <- clust.umap
umap.2$cluster.cluster <- as.character(clust.umap$cluster.cluster)
head(umap.2)

table(umap.2$cluster.cluster)

  2.1   2.2   2.3 
11937  7154  2708

Load umap of subclusters.

load("/Volumes/all_ssd/20220414-seurat/flox-integr-res-0.0120/flox-2-res-0.056/flox-2.1-res-0.232/umap-by-cluster-flox-2.1-res-0.232.Robj")
umap.2.1 <- clust.umap

load("/Volumes/all_ssd/20220414-seurat/flox-integr-res-0.0120/flox-2-res-0.056/flox-2.2-res-0.150/umap-by-cluster-flox-2.2-res-0.150.Robj")
umap.2.2 <- clust.umap

Recode cluster into subclusters.

umap.2[as.vector(rownames(umap.2.1 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "2.1.1"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "2.1.1"
umap.2[as.vector(rownames(umap.2.1 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "2.1.2"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "2.1.2"
umap.2[as.vector(rownames(umap.2.1 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "2.1.3"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "2.1.3"
umap.2[as.vector(rownames(umap.2.1 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "2.1.4"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "2.1.4"
umap.2[as.vector(rownames(umap.2.1 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "2.1.5"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "2.1.5"

umap.2[as.vector(rownames(umap.2.2 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "2.2.1"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "2.2.1"
umap.2[as.vector(rownames(umap.2.2 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "2.2.2"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "2.2.2"
umap.2[as.vector(rownames(umap.2.2 %>% filter(cluster.subclust == "2.2.3"))), "cluster.cluster"] <- "2.2.3"

umap.2$cluster.cluster <- factor(umap.2$cluster.cluster, levels = c("2.1.1", "2.1.2", "2.1.3", "2.1.4", "2.1.5", "2.2.1", "2.2.2", "2.2.3", "2.3"))

table(umap.2$cluster.cluster)

2.1.1 2.1.2 2.1.3 2.1.4 2.1.5 2.2.1 2.2.2 2.2.3   2.3 
 3624  3429  2856  1219   809  3835  2023  1296  2708

Generate label umap.

umap.label <- umap.2 %>% group_by(cluster.cluster) %>% summarize(umap.1 = median(umap.1), umap.2 = median(umap.2))

Generate cluster umap.

cluster.umap <- ggplot() +
geom_point(data = sample(umap.2), mapping = aes(x = umap.1, y = umap.2, color = cluster.cluster), shape = 20, stroke = 0, size = 0.5) +
geom_text(data = umap.label, mapping = aes(x = umap.1, y = umap.2, label = cluster.cluster), size = 2.3) +
labs(title = "Cluster 2, Nipbl Flox/+", x = "UMAP 1", y = "UMAP 2", color = "Cluster") +
  guides(color = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size = 2.3))) +
theme_classic(base_size = 7) +
theme(axis.line = element_blank(), axis.ticks = element_blank(), axis.text = element_blank(), plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 7), legend.key.size = unit(7, "pt"))

cluster.umap

clust.umap <- umap.2
save(clust.umap, file = "/Volumes/all_ssd/20220414-seurat/flox-integr-res-0.0120/flox-2-res-0.056/umap-by-cluster-flox-2-res-0.056-9.Robj")
ggsave(plot = cluster.umap, filename = "/Volumes/all_ssd/20220414-seurat/flox-integr-res-0.0120/flox-2-res-0.056/umap-by-cluster-flox-2-res-0.056-9.png", device = "png", width = 3.5, height = 2.15, units = "in")
